---
import NowHeroImage from "../assets/pages/hero-now.png";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import PersonLink from "../components/PersonLink.astro";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title="Now Page"
			description="What I'm doing now — inspired by Derek Sivers' now page movement."
		/>
		<style>
			.hero-image img {
				display: block;
				width: 100%;
				max-height: 440px;
				object-fit: cover;
				border-radius: 0;
			}
			@media (max-width: 720px) {
				.hero-image img { max-height: 220px; }
			}
			main {
				width: 760px;
				max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
				margin: auto;
				padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
			}
			.page-header {
				margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
				padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
				border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
			}
			.page-header h1 {
				margin: 0 0 0.25rem 0;
				font-size: 2rem;
			}
			.page-header p {
				margin: 0;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				font-size: 0.95rem;
			}
			@media (max-width: 720px) {
				main { width: 100%; max-width: 100%; padding: 1.5rem 1rem; }
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<div class="hero-image">
			<Image src={NowHeroImage} alt="Now page hero" loading="eager" />
		</div>
		<main>
			<div class="page-header">
				<h1>Now Page</h1>
				<p>A snapshot of what I'm focused on at this point in my life.</p>
			</div>

			<p>
				This is a <a href="https://nownownow.com/about">now page</a>.
				<PersonLink
					img_src="/profiles/sivers.png"
					name="Derek Sivers"
					link="https://sive.rs/"
				/> has inspired
				<a href="https://nownownow.com/">a growing number of "nowers"</a>
				to create these. If you have your own site, you should consider adding a
				<b>Now page</b> too.
			</p>

			<h2>Open Office Hours</h2>
			<p>
				If you know me — let's catch up. If you don't, let's meet.
				If you're in (or visiting) Krakow,
				<a href="/shorts/20251003a-where-to-meet/">here are some good spots to meet IRL</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>Working at DraftKings</h2>
			<p>
				I write code (mostly Elixir) at <a href="https://www.draftkings.com/">DraftKings</a>,
				one of the largest online sportsbooks and casinos. I get to work with some of the most
				supportive and talented people of my career.
			</p>

			<h2>Poland</h2>
			<p>
				I am an American with residency in Poland. I mostly work from our modest apartment but also
				have access to a co-working space near the city center in Krakow.
			</p>
			<p>I still maintain my home in Michigan and travel back often.</p>

			<h2>Nauka języka polskiego (Learning Polish)</h2>
			<p>
				I'm finally learning Polish. Progress is slow, but I'm really enjoying it. If you're also
				interested in learning Polish, I highly recommend
				<a href="https://e-polish.eu/polish-for-foreigners">Glossa</a> and they work with students
				worldwide. A special thank you to <PersonLink
					img_src="/profiles/magda.png"
					name="Magdalena Wyglądacz"
					link="https://e-polish.eu/en/polish_teachers_online/magdalena_wygladacz"
				/>, my ever patient (and professional) teacher!
			</p>

			<h2>Solo Projects</h2>
			<dl>
				<dt>Sprytna Cards</dt>
				<dd>I was inspired by people building useful little products, so I decided to try it myself.
				In about three months (and under $100), I launched <a href="https://sprytna.cards/">Sprytna.Cards</a>
				to beta. It is now out of beta but there are still some key features to add before I start promoting it.</dd>

				<dt>Greenway App</dt>
				<dd>Still in private/secure mode, it was built for people (or groups) to track property expenses,
				especially for rentals.</dd>

				<dt>Any One Will Do</dt>
				<dd>A randomizer like many others, but with the ability to add meta data for convenience.
				Like presentation links for presenters. <a href="https://anyonewilldo.com">Any One Will Do</a>.
				Although it sounds like it, it is not a dating app! :)</dd>

				<dt>Sprytna League</dt>
				<dd>A fun take on choosing the points your team will score each week. If your team scores at
				least as many points as you predict, you get the points you guessed (not more). If your team
				doesn't score as many points as you guessed, you get 0 points for the week. You can see a
				sample page at <a href="https://sprytnaleague.com">sprytnaleague.com</a> while I build out
				the platform.</dd>
			</dl>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
